v2.0.1 | Mar 10 2026:

  -- New Features --

[New] Monitor mode redesign: foreground supervisor replaces double-fork orphan model;
      -b/--background daemonizes supervisor; digest interval timer with hit escalation
      threshold; additive path composition via monitor_paths_extra; service files use
      Type=simple
[New] Config: digest_interval, digest_escalate_hits, monitor_paths_extra for monitor mode
[New] TSV canonical session format: 11-field hit records replace plaintext session files;
      scan, alert, monitor, and render pipelines migrated; session_legacy_compat config
      (auto/0/1) for backward compatibility with old sessions and report renderers
[New] JSON report output: --json-report [SCANID|list|newest] renders TSV sessions as
      JSON (v1.0 schema); --format text|json|html and --mailto ADDRESS
      position-independent report flags; graceful degradation for legacy sessions
[New] Compound signature (csig) scanning: multi-pattern boolean logic (AND/OR/threshold),
      case-insensitive matching (i:), wide UTF-16LE matching (w:), bounded gap wildcards
      ({N-M}); batch parallel workers; csig.dat and custom.csig.dat; prefix pre-screening
      optimization; scan_csig config var
[New] SHA-256 hash-based scanning: CPU hardware acceleration auto-detection (SHA-NI on
      x86, SHA2 on ARM); scan_hashtype config (auto/sha256/md5/both); sha256v2.dat
      signature file; ClamAV .hsb integration with version gate (>= 0.97);
      custom.sha256.dat for user-defined sigs
[New] Native batch scan engine: 43x faster end-to-end (1,217s to 28s on ~10,000 files);
      batch grep -F Aho-Corasick HEX matching with parallel workers; merged HEX+CSIG
      single worker pass; Perl dependency removed; ClamAV hex wildcard support
      (??, (aa|bb), *, nibble); scan_workers controls worker count (default: auto)
[New] Batch hit processing: unified bulk operations replace per-hit record_hit()+
      quarantine() fork loops across all scan engines; bulk stat+md5sum via xargs;
      batched chattr/chmod/chown for quarantine; ~12-15 fewer subprocess forks per hit
[New] Native YARA scanning: scan_yara=1 enables YARA as independent scan stage with
      yara or yr (YARA-X) binary; custom.yara and custom.yara.d/ drop-in directory;
      scan_yara_scope, compiled rules via yarac, --scan-list batch scanning for YARA
      >= 4.0; hookscan passes scan_yara; issue #392, #277, #239
[New] Email alerts reimagined: HTML+text dual-format with template engine ({{TOKEN}}
      placeholders); rfxn design language (teal brand bar, card-based threat entries);
      SMTP relay support (smtp_relay, smtp_from, smtp_user, smtp_pass); email_format
      config (text/html/both); Slack Block Kit, Telegram MarkdownV2, Discord embed
      templates; on-demand HTML rendering from session data
[New] Discord alerting: discord_alert and discord_webhook_url config; scan reports
      uploaded via Discord webhook multipart upload
[New] Shared library integrations: alert_lib (all alerting primitives), elog_lib
      (structured event logging with audit trail in /var/log/maldet/audit.log),
      tlog_lib (incremental log tracking, replaces 9 subprocess forks), pkg_lib
      (packaging primitives for install.sh/uninstall.sh; RPM/DEB infrastructure)
[New] ClamAV signature validation gate: clamscan -d validates sig files before
      deployment to ClamAV data directories; stage-validate-deploy pattern;
      sigup() SIGUSR2 reload gated on validation success; issue #467
[New] sigup_interval: independent 6-hourly signature update cron job via
      /etc/cron.d/maldet-sigup; --cron-sigup handler with flock serialization and
      0-120s random sleep; configurable interval (default 6h, 0 to disable)
[New] cron.watchdog: weekly watchdog script for independent fallback signature updates
      when primary cron.daily is broken or stale
[New] cron.daily: explicit cPanel addon/subdomain document root detection via
      /etc/userdatadomains; Bitrix panel detection; issue #268, #381
[New] -v/--version flag displays version information and exits 0

  -- Bug Fixes --

[Fix] Scan engine: isolate worker temp files using parent PID namespace ($$) to prevent
      concurrent scans from deleting each other's buffers during _scan_cleanup (F-SCAN-001)
[Fix] scan(): exit 1 when all provided scan paths do not exist; add _spaths_exist counter;
      empty file list now exits 1 only when zero paths resolved to filesystem entries (F-SCAN-002)
[Fix] _hash_batch_worker: detect md5sum/sha256sum backslash-escaped output; strip leading
      backslash from hash, use length($1)+3 for path offset, apply three-step sentinel
      unescape (\\→\001→\, \n→newline, \001→\) for filenames with \ or \n (F-ENG-001)
[Fix] _hex_csig_batch_worker: preload _match_dir SID files into local -A _loaded_sids
      before rule loop; _check_sid_match rewritten as O(1) array lookup; eliminates
      up to 40,000 grep forks per scan cycle under complex CSIG rules (F-ENG-002)
[Fix] _hex_csig_batch_worker: preload hex sigmap into local -A _sigmap_cache at worker
      start; replace both _hex_lookup_name call sites with O(1) array lookups; eliminates
      one awk fork per HEX hit (F-ENG-003)
[Fix] scan_strlen: add os_freebsd guard at function entry; logs {strlen} skip message
      rather than silently failing with wc -L (GNU extension not available on FreeBSD) (F-ENG-004)
[Fix] Monitor mode: replace string variable with array for inotifywait --exclude arguments
      to prevent startup failure when ignore paths contain spaces (F-MON-002)
[Fix] Monitor mode: replace greedy awk sub() with match() in _monitor_filter_events
      to prevent path truncation and malware bypass (F-MON-001)
[Fix] Monitor mode: 8 defects fixed (graceful shutdown, inline loop, ERE escape,
      kernel check, ClamAV cache, batch filter, crash recovery, session rotation)
[Fix] Monitor runtime: remove double ClamAV scan; guard empty PID; compat.conf
      reload order matches startup; unbounded accumulation of find-filter strings;
      user count via awk UID threshold; batch native scan path; issue #454, #447, #459
[Fix] Alerting: Slack migrated from deprecated files.upload API to
      files.getUploadURLExternal + files.completeUploadExternal; Telegram /bot prefix;
      token security via curl -K; panel alert signature names and path handling;
      genalert() state isolation; issue #387, #458, #461, #426
[Fix] Config security: _safe_source_conf() allowlist (79 variables) replaces blocklist;
      blocks PATH/LD_PRELOAD/IFS overrides from remote config; -co CLI flag uses same
      parser; rejects metacharacters, command substitution, and pipes
[Fix] Config import: remote config RCE prevention; config source order corrected to
      match documented loading order; conf.maldet permissions preserved at 640 after
      upgrade; sigup_interval re-evaluated after _import_config() on upgrade
[Fix] ClamAV: empty lmd.user.ndb/hdb no longer deployed to ClamAV data dirs;
      gensigs() linksigs ordering corrected; temp file used as scan target for
      older ClamAV (exits 2 on device files); portable command rm/cp alias bypass
[Fix] view_report(): on-demand text rendering from TSV; "newest" and empty scan ID
      resolve to most recent session; list mode 6→1 file reads per session; sendmail
      path no longer prepends SUBJECT: header into session files; issue #336
[Fix] Security hardening: lmdup() validates upstream version string against semver
      to prevent directory traversal; hookscan.sh validates ModSecurity filenames;
      --user flag validates username against path traversal; JSON injection via
      _json_escape(); email subject CR/LF stripped to prevent header injection
[Fix] File permissions hardened: conf.maldet 0644 → 0640; sigdir, logdir, tmpdir,
      and audit log directory 755 → 750; custom sig files restricted to 640/750
      when pubscan disabled
[Fix] Quarantine system: TOCTOU mv exit code check; inode naming replaces $RANDOM;
      batch quarantine signature name; colon truncation in .info/quarantine.hist/
      session.hits paths; batch dedup guard; issue #399
[Fix] sigignore(): permanently deleted from on-disk sig files on every scan; moved
      ignore filtering to runtime copies in gensigs(); signatures no longer
      irrecoverably lost between signature updates
[Fix] CLI robustness: 19 bare exit statements given explicit codes; -c, -x, -i, -q,
      -n, -s, --web-proxy reject missing/empty arguments; -a validates scan path
      existence before dispatch; issue #366
[Fix] install.sh: man page compression on fresh install; backup robustness; upgrade
      no longer kills inotify monitoring; Slackware init per rc.NAME convention;
      MONITOR_MODE migration ordering; preserve hookscan config and pub/ state;
      issue #414
[Fix] FreeBSD: detection via uname -s replacing broken $OSTYPE check; id -u (POSIX)
      replaces id --user; restore() touch -t for mtime restoration; /dev/fd avoidance
      in _batch_record_hits(); portable command cp/mv/rm throughout
[Fix] clamselector(): logs warning on clamd test failure instead of silently switching;
      no longer overwrites user scan_max_filesize; remove invalid --fdpass from remote
      clamd TCP path; issue #452, #410
[Fix] cron.daily: flock lock leak to backgrounded scans; lockfile prevents overlapping
      runs; dead code in update failure logging; config errors propagate to cron;
      issue #373
[Fix] find/ignore: ignore_file_ext, --exclude-regex, --include-regex, ignore_paths
      converted to bash arrays for correct find argument passing; scan_ignore_user/
      group handles non-existent user/group; find_recentopts escaping fixed;
      issue #446, #438, #450, #72, #335, #440
[Fix] gensigs(): ClamAV MD5 merge format corrected for custom user signatures;
      temp file leak on repeated calls; _count_signatures() counts from on-disk
      files instead of runtime variables (always reported 0 CSIG/SHA-256 in sigup)
[Fix] Alert rendering: hit type regex handles {MD5}/{CSIG}/{SHA256} prefixes; empty
      quarpath consecutive-tab field shift in text reports; JSON injection in
      Slack/Discord templates; empty SUMMARY_* tokens in single-hit messaging
[Fix] tlog trim cursor unit mismatch: purge() and monitor_cycle() subtracted byte
      count from line-count cursor; issue #227; replace ed dependency for log
      trimming, preserving file inode; issue #308
[Fix] Miscellaneous portability: mktemp replaces $RANDOM/$$; command -v replaces
      which; grep -E replaces egrep; POSIX ':' chown separator; sed -E for portability;
      quote critical variable expansions; hardcoded binary paths replaced with
      command -v discovered variables
[Fix] restore() and restore_hitlist(): return exit 1 on all error paths; automated
      recovery scripts checking $? previously saw false success on invalid scan ID
      or nonexistent file

  -- Changes --

[Change] Library decomposition: functions monolith (6,086 lines, 107 functions)
         split into 11 sub-libraries under files/internals/ with lmd.lib.sh sourcing
         hub; maldet source chain simplified from 9 statements to 2; functions
         retained as backward-compat shim
[Change] Config import: _import_config() rewritten with pkg_config_merge() AWK merge;
         importconf heredoc template deleted (~440 lines); 17 compat variable
         migrations + 3 special-case migrations preserved
[Change] Scan engine: HEX+CSIG merged into single worker pass (~17x faster CSIG via
         set-based rule evaluation); scan stage reorder (strlen runs last, reducing
         wasted work on FP-prone stage); bulk awk HEX classifier (~5s to <0.3s
         compilation)
[Change] Performance: ~500,000 fork/exec operations eliminated by replacing external
         command pipelines with Bash builtins across scan, quarantine, monitor, and
         alerting paths
[Change] HTML email rendered on-demand at send time from current templates; persistent
         .html session files no longer stored; responsive 700px layout with Outlook
         compatibility; clean scans show "No Threats Detected" celebration block
[Change] CLI: modifier flags (-x, -i, -hscan, -qd, --format, --mailto) are now
         position-independent; -qd with non-existent directory exits 1 instead of
         silent ignore; -qd override preserved when combined with -U/--user
[Change] Documentation: man page rewritten following man-pages(7) conventions; README
         expanded with 28 missing config variables, Discord alerting, YARA batch
         scanning, hookscan; --help rewritten with categorized sections and complete
         option coverage
[Change] Rename sig_import_*_url config variables (from import_custsigs_*_url) for
         sig_* namespace consistency; compat.conf migration maps old names; install.sh
         migrates on upgrade
[Change] scan_workers default changed from "0" to "auto"; "0" silently accepted as
         auto for backward compat
[Change] Update verification prefers SHA-256 over MD5; graceful MD5 fallback when
         sha256sum absent; _verify_download() helper eliminates inline duplication
[Change] maldet.service: EnvironmentFile changed from conf.maldet to
         /etc/sysconfig/maldet or /etc/default/maldet; ExecStart uses
         ${MONITOR_MODE:-users}; init script uses -b daemonization
[Change] -E/--dump-report suppressed from help; case handler retained for backward compat
[Change] inotify_verbose per-file ClamAV logging deprecated; batch engine log
         messages supersede
[Change] Vendored libraries updated: tlog_lib v2.0.4, elog_lib v1.0.4, alert_lib
         v1.0.5, pkg_lib v1.0.5; batsman submodule v1.2.2
[Change] _scan_progress(): plain newline-terminated output in non-TTY contexts
         (cron, pipe, docker exec); ANSI escape sequences gated behind TTY check
